Setup ros2 holoocean workspace in a container:

For ubuntu 22.04 follow the instructions here:
https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads?target_os=Linux&target_arch=x86_64&Distribution=Ubuntu&target_version=22.04&target_type=deb_local

Install cuda 12.5 and nvidia driver (my computer 555)

Follow these instructions for the container toolkit:

https://docs.nvidia.com/datacenter/cloud-native/container-toolkit/1.16.0/install-guide.html

Install docker: Docker version 20.10.17, build 100c701


HOLOOCEAN:

Sign the unreal agreements

Clone the source code from: https://github.com/byu-holoocean/HoloOcean

pip install the holoocean python package following installation instructions:
	https://byu-holoocean.github.io/holoocean-docs/v1.0.0/index.html
Install the holoocean world



Install the ro2 packages into the ros2 workspace from 
https://github.com/byu-holoocean/holoocean-ros/tree/main

colcon build inside the ros2 workspace and run

source install/setup.bash
ros2 launch holoocean_main holoocean_full_launch.py



#DOCKER setup:
make the docker build command run the pip installation and copy the source code and world in?


Make sure you have
- container toolkit
- nvidia driver
- run xhost +



